<br>
To answer your question, Lazo, specifically, no, I wouldn't call you a homophobe because you dislike, or are even disgusted by, certain sexual behaviours.  I don't rip on people who don't like oral sex, I don't rip on people who don't like certain sexual positions, and I don't rip on people who don't like gay sex.  So, as long as you aren't hateful toward gay people because of your dislike, you just have dislikes, which are perfectly normal.<br>
<br>
The problem is, when the discussion is about the sigs, it's about behaviour toward people because of their sexual behaviours or preferences.  The people who object to the sigs because of their *gay* content rather than their *sexual* content don't just have preferences, they're discriminating.<br>
<br>
I respect people who are okay with all kinds of sexual sigs, that's their choice.<br>
<br>
I respect people who dislike all sexual sigs, or certain levels of sexual sigs, and want a more restrictive standard on what's acceptable, gay or straight.  That's their choice, and I&quot;m starting to agree with them.<br>
<br>
I even respect people who are okay with &quot;straight&quot; sigs, yet don't like the &quot;gay&quot; ones, and still concede that to be fair, both must be allowed.<br>
<br>
But people who say that a sig that involves two people of the opposite sex engaged in sexual behaviour is okay, while a similar sig with two men or two women is &quot;disgusting&quot; and should be banned...that's homophobic, and I can't respect that.<br>
<br>
(And before anyone says it, yes, I know that some people who objected to the sig do so not because of the gender of the characters involved but because of other factors...but many seem to just focus on the fact that it's two guys. *shrug*)<br>
<br>
